history.content: Being a regents scholar, you are definitely fine.

@5205

If you sign up for dis and lab sections that have space and so are enrolled before the last undergrad phase 2 appointment has passed, then you should be fine. If you waitlist for popular sections, your priority no longer functions after that date.

I'm a freshman in EECS planning on taking CS 61B next semester. I'm a regents scholar so I get priority registration in Phase I and Phase II (I believe). I'm wondering if it is necessary to enroll in CS61B during Phase I. I would prioritize getting into CS classes but want to also make sure that I end up in sections for H/SS classes I would enjoy. As of now, I have enrolled in EE16B and two non-technicals. I thought it would be OK to enroll in 61B phase II because of EECS reserved seating and because my phase II is earlier than that of other freshmen. Looking to get an instructors perspective.

Thanks!
